<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Reference configuration (NOT wired into this module's live build) for the FORMAT layer of the reference
  stack: Spotless orchestrating google-java-format, with the new-code-focused ratchetFrom the gate design
  uses. It is shown here rather than executed because the SOURCE-PIN identifier "Spotless 8.7.0" is the
  project / Gradle-plugin release line and does not resolve as a Maven-plugin coordinate (the
  spotless-maven-plugin is versioned on its own line); the Maven-plugin version literal is therefore left
  as the ${spotless.maven.plugin.version} property to set at pin time, so the build asserts no unpinned
  coordinate. See 09-flags/34_spotless_maven_plugin_version_unresolved.md.

  google-java-format is pinned to the SOURCE-PIN value (1.35.0, min JDK 21). Pinning the formatter GAV is
  the chapter's point: a formatter's rendering can shift between its own versions, so it is pinned, not
  floated. The alternative named in the stack — palantir-java-format — is a different fixed opinion that
  would slot in as <palantirJavaFormat> in the same place; the choice of formatter matters far less than
  picking one and automating it, which is why the layer is swappable without disturbing the rest.

  ratchetFrom scopes formatting to files changed since the trunk — the same new-code focus the gate design
  applies, so the format layer is adoptable on a legacy codebase without rewriting the whole tree at once.

  To activate: set the spotless.maven.plugin.version property to the pinned spotless-maven-plugin version,
  then `mvn -B spotless:check` (in the gate) and `mvn -B spotless:apply` (rewrite locally / pre-commit).
-->
<plugin xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0">
  <!-- tag::spotless-reference[] -->
  <groupId>com.diffplug.spotless</groupId>
  <artifactId>spotless-maven-plugin</artifactId>
  <version>${spotless.maven.plugin.version}</version> <!-- pin at /pin-source -->
  <configuration>
    <ratchetFrom>origin/main</ratchetFrom> <!-- format only files changed since trunk -->
    <java>
      <googleJavaFormat><version>1.35.0</version></googleJavaFormat>
    </java>
  </configuration>
  <!-- end::spotless-reference[] -->
</plugin>
